Harmony Pena – User Story 1


Actors:
• Student: An individual that is a part of a team/group project

Name: Team Meetings Integration
Created by: Harmony Jackson (Pena)

Actors involved: 
•	Triggered actor: Student
•	Secondary actor: N/a

Brief Description: A student can click a link and join a live video/audio conference with their team (using any outside conferencing platform)

Triggering Event(s): Student click on the conference link
Priority: Medium

Preconditions: A specific date and time is agreed on by all students/team members
Assumptions: A conference link is created by a team member and added to the team’s calendar

The flow of events:
1.	A meeting date & time is created by a student/group member
2.	A student attaches/adds a direct link for the live meeting
3.	A student clicks on the link 
4.	The student is asked if it’s okay to leave the app platform to join a meeting on a different platform
5.	The student accepts to exit the app to join the meeting
6.	The student joins the team conference

Alternative/Abnormal flow of events: 
1.	The student does not accept leaving the calendar app to join the meeting, the case ends

Postconditions: The student is directed to the team conference call
Non-functional Requirements:
-	Students must click on the link and is not does automatically join
---------------
User Stories:
1.	As a student, I want to be able to speak to my group in a live conferencing environment, so that we can discuss tasks and assignments to complete our project.
